                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/653: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Einstein</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Prague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-10T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 10, 1929—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 10—12:23 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>59. Your circular telegram of December 1, 4 p.m. Ministry of Foreign Affairs
                    informs me that yesterday Dr. Benes sent a telegram to Shanghai and today he
                    addresses a note to the Soviet representative at Prague to say that Czechoslovak
                    Government adheres to American point of view.<note n="99" xml:id="d369fn99">The
                        Czechoslovak Legation confirmed this action on December 11 (861.77 Chinese
                        Eastern/732).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Einstein</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
